<h2>Scaled Difference Panel</h2>


<p>The <strong>Scaled Difference</strong> panel lets you exaggerate the 
distance between multiple surfaces. This exaggeration does not effect 
the surface properties and intersection points.


<br><br>
<dl><dd>
<img src="nvimg/panel/scale_diff.gif" alt="Scaled Difference Panel" width="288" height="126">
</dd></dl>
<br><br>



<h3>OPTIONS</h3>

<dl>

<dt> <strong>Reference Surface</strong></dt>
<dd>Shows the name(s) of all the loaded surfaces. Use this menu to select
the reference surface. 
<br><br></dd>

<dt> <strong>Exag</strong></dt>
<dd>Sets the exaggeration difference between the reference and other 
surfaces.
<br><br></dd>

<dt> <strong>None</strong></dt>
<dd>Turns off the scaled difference and unselects the reference surface.
<br><br></dd>

<dt> <strong>Close</strong></dt>
<dd>Closes the <strong>Scaled Difference</strong> panel.
<br><br></dd>

</dl>


